Citations
Date:  0/0/1984
Source:  Waiouru: Land of the Tussock 1935-40
Author:  ARTHUR
Vol / Page:  19

Edition:
Quote:  The stacker or his off-sider, known as a crow, gives a signal and the grab-man pulls a rope which releases the two arms of the grab from the hay. Then back comes the boom and down comes the grab to get more hay ad infinitum. I was grab-man today and it wasn't so bad this afternoon.
